with a clockwise component more freely than they get pushed along paths with counterclockwise

115
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:18,820
components, well that would mean that the resonance with right-handed circularly polarized

116
00:07:18,820 --> 00:07:23,560
light would be a little different from what it is for left-handed circularly polarized light,

117
00:07:23,940 --> 00:07:27,580
and hence the indices of refraction would be slightly different for each one.

118
00:07:27,580 --> 00:07:32,900
When you combine this together with the fact that the resonance depends on the frequency of the

119
00:07:32,900 --> 00:07:38,360
light, which is to say it depends on the color, this ultimately explains why the optical rotation

