00:11:25,180 --> 00:11:30,980
when you express a pulse of light as a sum of many pure sine waves, even if the phase velocities of

164
00:11:30,980 --> 00:11:36,240
those constituent components go faster than c, that doesn't necessarily imply that the center of

165
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:41,480
mass of this pulse will itself go faster than c. And in fact, when you simulate the effect of

166
00:11:41,480 --> 00:11:45,780
passing through a medium, when the index of refraction is less than one, what you find is a

167
00:11:45,780 --> 00:11:51,800
pulse that goes slower than c, even when the crests within it are going faster. And if that still seems

168
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:57,020
a bit weird, here's an analogy to help see why phase velocity can be way higher than the speed

169
00:11:57,020 --> 00:12:02,560
of anything real. Imagine a little machine that has a bunch of rotating arms all extending from

170
00:12:02,560 --> 00:12:08,480
a shared shaft. If you view this machine from the side, the tips of all of those arms form what looks

171
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:14,840
like a wave, with crests traveling from right to left. But if I go and reposition the arms to be

172
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:20,100
angled quite close to each other, then you can make it so that the phase velocity of this emergent

173
00:12:20,100 --> 00:12:25,680
wave is arbitrarily high, potentially faster than the speed of light or anything else, even when the

174
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:30,640
shaft is rotating at a gentle constant rate, and even when every component of the machine is moving

175
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:35,680
at a reasonably slow pace. Here, it's pretty obvious that such a machine doesn't violate the

176
00:12:35,680 --> 00:12:40,540
rules of physics, and that it doesn't let you send messages faster than light, because the wave crest

177
00:12:40,540 --> 00:12:44,880
is not a real object. It's not something that could carry information. It's more of an illusion.

178
00:12:45,440 --> 00:12:50,740
The phase velocity in a light wave is similar. Sure, if you shine an x-ray through glass, it is

179
00:12:50,740 --> 00:12:55,620
true that the wave crests go faster than the speed of light, but the underlying influences between

180
00:12:55,620 --> 00:13:02,120
electric charges that determine the field values in the first place are themselves all bound by the speed c.

